Actor Titilope Kuti’ aka Ade Tiger is well known for his role in “King of Boys: The Return of the King.” In a chat with Hip Tv, the TV personality said he has learnt to live with being called ‘Ade Tiger’ all the time. According to him, the name is very much welcomed as it goes that show that he gave an impressionable delivery of his role in the movie to have earned it in real life. He said: “As a matter of fact, it’s a welcome development. It only means that the character gave people such an experience that they feel connected to it. So it’s not a bad thing.   Madonna announces collaboration with Fireboy DML     15th Headies holds in Atlanta, Bentley for next rated act     Reactions over Fireboy DML’s picture with Madonna   “People called Arnold Schwarzenegger ‘Commando’ for at least 20-25 years. “Same thing goes for ‘Rambo’ who is Sylvester Stallone. So it’s alright. “Up until the next time I do something that is more monumental, I mean, it’s welcome. “Ade Tiger, Titi Kuti, one and the same.” The ‘Ade Tiger’ character in King of Boys 1 transitioned to one of the main characters in King of Boys ‘The return of the King’ which got Nigerians talking.